2025-02-19 14:36:29,tell about shivaji's family .,Shivaji I belonged to the Bhonsle clan, a Maratha family. His father, Shahaji Bhonsle, was a Maratha general serving the Deccan Sultanates.  His mother was Jijabai, daughter of Lakhuji Jadhavrao of Sindhkhed, a Mughal-aligned sardar claiming Yadav descent from Devagiri. His paternal grandfather, Maloji (1552–1597), was an influential general of the Ahmadnagar Sultanate, titled ""Raja,"" and held deshmukhi rights in several areas.  Shivaji had at least four wives: Sai Bhonsale (died 1659), Soyarabai, Putalabai, and Sakvarbai, and Kashibai Jadhav. He had eight children, including Sambhaji and Rajaram I.  Shivaji's half-brother, Venkoji (Ekoji I), was Shahaji's son by his second wife, Tukabai (née Mohite), and ruled Thanjavur.
